<body data-page="about">

  <!-- Header -->
  <%- include('partials/header') %>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <main class="main-content">

    <!-- ===================================================== -->
    <!-- 1️⃣ WRDA AT A GLANCE -->
    <!-- ===================================================== -->
    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>WRDA at a Glance</h2>

      <p>
        Wonta Rural Development Association (WRDA) is committed to empowering rural communities by implementing 
        sustainable development programs in education, healthcare, agriculture, women empowerment, and income generation.
      </p>

      <p>
        Our organization works closely with local leaders, youth, farmers, and families to understand community needs 
        and build solutions that create long-term, meaningful change.
      </p>

      <!-- Gallery -->
      <div class="moving-gallery">
        <img id="about-image2" src="/images/about2.jpg" alt="Development Program">
      </div>

      <p>
        Through collaboration, innovation, and community-led initiatives, WRDA continues to strengthen rural resilience 
        and improve the quality of life for underserved communities.
      </p>
    </section>



    <!-- ===================================================== -->
    <!-- 2️⃣ MISSION & VISION -->
    <!-- ===================================================== -->

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Mission & Vision</h2>

      <h3>Our Mission</h3>
      <p>
        To support and uplift rural communities through sustainable development initiatives that improve education, 
        health, agriculture, and income generation.
      </p>

      <h3>Our Vision</h3>
      <p>
        A future where every rural community has access to equal opportunities, essential services, and the resources 
        needed for long-term well-being.
      </p>

      <h3>What We Do</h3>
      <ul class="about-list">
        <li><strong>Education:</strong> School support, teacher training, and youth leadership programs.</li>
        <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Medical outreach, health education, and community clinics.</li>
        <li><strong>Agriculture:</strong> Farmer training, irrigation systems, and sustainable agriculture support.</li>
        <li><strong>Women Empowerment:</strong> Skills training, financial inclusion, and leadership development.</li>
        <li><strong>Community Development:</strong> Clean water, environmental protection, and local capacity building.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>



    <!-- ===================================================== -->
    <!-- 3️⃣ WRDA LEADERSHIP -->
